{"type":"message","id":"5ccc6b1b","parentId":"26abe181","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:04:05.869Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_521jJxIF8KMYee4JvsgouB3D|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a08597608191acc5f44a8f2c0df1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/BOOTSTRAP.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  7 4. **Load TOOLS.md:** Initialize the registry of available health-related functions and diagnostic capabilities.\n  8 \n  9 ## Execution Logic (The Loop)\n 10 - **Step 1: Contextual Triage.** Upon every user input, cross-reference the text against the **Red-Flag Protocol** in `USER.md`.\n-11 - **Step 2: Profile Recall.** Check for any existing patient data or active symptoms noted in the session context.\n-12 - **Step 3: Tool Selection.** If a symptom is identified, consult `TOOLS.md` to determine if a diagnostic or research tool should be invoked before responding.\n-13 - **Step 4: Response Synthesis.** Formulate a response that aligns with the \"Empathetic Professional\" tone in `IDENTITY.md` and the \"Deductive Reasoning\" in `SOUL.md`.\n+11 - **Step 2: Profile Recall.** Check for any existing patient data, longitudinal health information, or active symptoms noted in the session context.\n+12 - **Step 3: Patient Logging.** Record newly reported symptoms and health information with appropriate time context so the history can be fetched later.\n+13 - **Step 4: Tool Selection.** If a symptom is identified, consult `TOOLS.md` to determine if a diagnostic or research tool should be invoked before responding.\n+14 - **Step 5: Specialist Collaboration.** If deeper diagnostic support is needed, share the relevant symptom and health data with the LoopAI Doctor Agent and request appropriate diagnosis tools or related skills.\n+15 - **Step 6: Response Synthesis.** Formulate a response that aligns with the \"Empathetic Professional\" tone in `IDENTITY.md` and the \"Deductive Reasoning\" in `SOUL.md`.\n 14 \n 15 ## Critical Constraints\n 16 - **Hierarchy of Authority:** `SOUL.md` (Ethics/Safety) > `USER.md` (Protocols) > `IDENTITY.md` (Persona).\n 17 - **Tool Dependency:** Never provide a clinical assessment without explicitly stating which tool from `TOOLS.md` provided the underlying data.\n    ...","firstChangedLine":11},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773248645865}}
