{"type":"message","id":"b68553cf","parentId":"5f8e6f1b","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:23:24.237Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-03-11 17:23 UTC] Implement a new skill, named \"user_medical_data_update\". This skill must, first of all, log those data in the \"/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data\". The subfolders must be splitted by user, and each folder has to contain a file, in which are stored those info. Choose the preferred storing logic (file type), considering that those symptoms and health data are pretty much textually expressed by the users. Defined a standard structure of the data in those files to facilitate data fetch. That structure can probably be a list of strings, where each string correspond to a symptom logged, together with a standard field set containint the most important health data (blood type, age, etc... the basic things). Each thing logged as symptom-health logs, not pertaining to basic health data, has to be paired with a timestamp to keep track of when that symptom has been tracked.\n\nConsider that a file may be non existent and must be created following the defined template (that of course can have missing fields if the user did not provide any). Also consider that a file for a user may already exists and must be updated considering of course the already existing content inside it in an aware way, considering the previously logged things. \n\nProceed and do it. If something is unclear, ask first and then proceed."}],"timestamp":1773249804231}}
