ut committing the workspace, it doesn't seem relevant right now. I should focus on what's most important and not get too caught up in the smaller details. It's all about prioritizing the key aspects!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Implemented.\n\n### What I built\nI created a new skill at:\n\n- `/home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update`\n\nand packaged it at:\n\n- `/home/node/.openclaw/skills/dist/user-medical-data-update.skill`\n\n### Storage design\nI chose **JSON** as the storage format, because it fits text-heavy symptom/history data while still making fetch/update logic structured and reliable.\n\nEach user record is stored at:\n\n- `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data/<sanitized-user-id>/medical_data.json`\n\n### Record structure\nEach file contains:\n\n- `schema_version`\n- `user_id`\n- `created_at`\n- `updated_at`\n- `basic_health_data`\n- `symptom_health_timeline`\n\n`basic_health_data` holds stable profile fields such as:\n- full name\n- preferred name\n- date of birth\n- age\n- sex\n- gender\n- blood type\n- height\n- weight\n- allergies\n- chronic conditions\n- medications\n- emergency contact\n- primary physician\n- notes\n\n`symptom_health_timeline` holds timestamped entries such as:\n- symptoms\n- health notes\n- measurements\n- diagnosis history\n- medication updates\n\n### Behavior implemented\nThe bundled script:\n\n- creates the user folder if missing\n- creates `medical_data.json` from template if missing\n- preserves prior content\n- updates scalar fields only when a new non-empty value is provided\n- merges unique list fields like allergies/medications\n- appends new timeline entries\n- skips exact duplicate timeline items\n- sorts the timeline by timestamp\n\n### Files created\n- `/home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/SKILL.md`\n- `/home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/references/schema.md`\n- `/home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/scripts/update_user_medical_data.py`\n\n### Validation\nI tested:\n- initial file creation\n- later merge into an existing user file\n- dedupe behavior for repeated symptom entries\n\nOne small note: I normalized the filesystem/package skill name to `user-medical-data-update` to match skill naming rules, while implementing the exact functionality you requested for “user_medical_data_update”.\n\nIf you want, I can next:\n1. wire this skill into your agent instructions so it gets used automatically when users report symptoms, and/or  \n2. create a companion fetch skill for reading a user’s medical history back in a structured way.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a58c35808191a769f78c10208d07\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":435,"output":559,"cacheRead":29952,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30946,"cost":{"input":0.0010875000000000001,"output":0.008385,"cacheRead":0.007488,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0169605}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773249925693}}
