{"type":"message","id":"5facb0b9","parentId":"209a2832","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:29:38.149Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to make sure I’m giving safe medical advice without making any diagnoses. It’s also clear that I should highlight that the user should seek urgent care if they feel their situation is severe. This way, I can provide support while also emphasizing the importance of professional help. I’ll mention that their message has been logged successfully as well. Keeping those points in mind is really important for guiding the user effectively!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a67ba5d8819188f154c0bde2a380\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpsaZ9poXY1IfvTbUSkBpjgkoajpghPCPDnV226ZKstM0erc8Y6Qv2y_kkrpAHumf1OFErbPLhPBC2tLbLq-YsRRxn5MgaZFq0QmqSTmfYh5AvMzGqq3z4c7APZO4ogqxBYAen92yZ9jgE4aYwZEw3qYVZn5c99j52Hog8exTXHr8usQ8TFcqMxBpLx6BBduhZfEUSQPi1ZDQBoiiJIyYrawMUT2ynskuqZD3qnrcgoAACNuPR48KYaBICzpNzA1EdK47OqRjloyLioL_vUh07P1liSoDSY5E4PFwqChHjd3li13zp7sp19LWpuNoF1GI7wG8o8bIU9T003A-Z8ro3RO0gtyC_GkPLmZ-udMtwIszpTUmFaPbH0cxL32Iff59U_iT9buGz_xwAnQnSxF5HH10hoaIit9t1zqeyI6PatjBfrnz93I3jiaogx_mV4PbMCiDbRhmqw2Yd9K9RFGDdmyfY1E1wByZLFpbyKv0VICChgnXu6OZLqjVF7okVuy0sNsqlHE2D4j-sNc-I0_HJ8-gUlaVzGh_xcbizB0yQz_bFu1_vd2kdTLS9n7MRROY_qtouzRmc4u6ZyuG3iHdwyEitqpedeapuOJjjkZcaOYAn1X7Bx_WyUE2fezGMXe-YXiM0TBdxU8bFcARyIjNB083YK-YYbUvhIboAnAcbJzyW1gRV3-UvXGX7syCoSBQ5DSny9_tn2IUgjVnyRfi4lqDIcDaIBYFNq-iBdVuWCEoP4GReDwZ7iMAw-Gcf-o6PMlbKAA5u9l-bR98iKOFKlD-LyZ_OUM3YzxshMhEj2K8KZic91m9DeVqoO-17sT-Q78YHX9Au-hDyrlyMrCXozll2t5kKvxSALkNTDr0HcdLwTb_NxeNMuoEhuiHcexQYfU3_GGdyd92mwFhICpHwoldyul7oQ7JyWvxBvg5XGFO64AHcdoxZXwdFHyokESddVfrm\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"I need to make sure I’m giving safe medical advice without making any diagnoses. It’s also clear that I should highlight that the user should seek urgent care if they feel their situation is severe. This way, I can provide support while also emphasizing the importance of professional help. I’ll mention that their message has been logged successfully as well. Keeping those points in mind is really important for guiding the user effectively!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Yes — the logging test worked. I stored your reported data as a structured record with age **28**, plus these timestamped entries: **headache all day**, **red-ish eyes all day**, and **not sleeping well**.\n\nAs for what it could be: this combination is **not specific to one illness**, but common possibilities include:\n- **sleep deprivation / eye strain**\n- **dry eyes or eye irritation**\n- **allergies**\n- **tension headache**\n- **dehydration**\n- sometimes **viral illness** or **migraine**\n\nRed eyes plus headache can also happen with prolonged screen use, poor sleep, or irritation, but if the eye redness is paired with **eye pain, blurred vision, sensitivity to light, nausea/vomiting, or one-sided severe headache**, that needs **urgent medical evaluation**, because some eye conditions can be serious.\n\nA few focused questions to narrow it down:\n1. Is the headache **mild, moderate, or severe**?\n2. Is it **on one side**, or all over your head?\n3. Do you have **blurred vision**, **eye pain**, or **light sensitivity**?\n4. Any **fever**, **runny nose**, **itching**, or **watering eyes**?\n5. Have you had **a lot of screen time**, poor hydration, or caffeine changes today?\n\nI can help you reason through the likely causes step by step, but this is only a **preliminary assessment**, not a final diagnosis. Does that make sense, or would you like me to clarify any part of that?","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a67d97508191bc3fd8194ef10746\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":534,"output":355,"cacheRead":30720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31609,"cost":{"input":0.001335,"output":0.005325,"cacheRead":0.007679999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014339999999999999}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773250169704}}
{"type":"message","id":"a6fc0099","parentId":"5facb0b9","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:38:35.361Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-03-11 17:38 UTC] i like what you did, fine. at the moment, i see two \"sample\" folders, which is the logic of naming of a folder?"}],"timestamp":1773250715356}}
{"type":"message","id":"058be911","parentId":"a6fc0099","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:38:43.446Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Explaining folder naming**\n\nI’m working on how to explain folder naming. It seems like I don't need any previous memory for this task. For example, I might use sample test folder names like \"sample-user-123\" and \"webchat-current-user.\" I want to make it clear, so users understand the significance of using descriptive names for better organization. It's important to keep things straightforward while providing clear examples!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a89ceb888191a25cacb160d60ee1\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpsaifQX5mXpvIty3S_KVh7FLgZE0-hO35ciplNtIAvlczZfEVCb1bcFs8UcRMlVPvdKLX8x88hoemxaLEmvQGfNkW1d_w0RqsGX-nZfZIgO8dgslI-hdf2C5z6udPcaDiOMC2w5lkP5bEyeKXUiTp1PTdw1mwaRgMnMh_O8NP9Xuynur41Z_9x92XkGpkXkjSSadDmAhYGn7x3gCtkVCltXqoCYFsWvcq6q4y7xmzMTzGzh0GEQst1A8e4kxlVLLCZIfxzLvWUjZWqBgFrkjfVsTYntjQCEbmU4WKowarG_XvoIKjZZCgVIkjCnujHlTwEqTnkn0JXO3eb9NYxEaOLVNzSPFjOrONGWirtdLtAtwZvU_-NscZGI13OUiWCNQSJkAYIkzZL44sV-7XFpxgkVEMpavdQiwAVLTbPq_yUsJeQw9YfvS6RzKcLQpPjEPBSIdtIF8gP9mn_nv0-lmkOJUuewvIiPrNPHatwFXTGKpr6SDfXAPcudeyUAiXbJ7f3aN1oQP6FVY2qe6Ec_HTqrnYUCMhRK9CF6z7CYj_mE9r7E8dAoSQIU2-GqSgMSDan4larJEDvpMijbXIwO33-UGMOV10HSYthLzsy_6wPkMjcXeLKt0dzasIvTpFSFiVeOOpk1gI08H5udZQ2W5PAGq3dpBFxYcfX750A4Wvx5I1WtoE2IXcmMcMrPZn4ykqH9phBdKZxrWyToCptAftTV0b2s1srrHkw-H_RFgumyMD3WIQbMj2QZSqDdipmGVXjKwbnG5fbo5SD0JOADIHw9hN1dYPyLwEuIuSMZrSAp-wc0CEn5v0cHLpTbW_Ttpu0d7xjSufV7NmxFelkG67v07ErVb7wGLbph0nbV9XLKq6CCMhSRA_pc5zNxl2-TISlyrvJ5QMdhInghPLYkwS9KeFeomwJg-fhDtofv9iBYCM2TN8PDKqJUPNtKxxiiXcR8uFhGAJhmyGPFk7Dwt3A3N-7wJ_AaFgPOKyfWM-wMgkJ88=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Explaining folder naming**\\n\\nI’m working on how to explain folder naming. It seems like I don't need any previous memory for this task. For example, I might use sample test folder names like \\\"sample-user-123\\\" and \\\"webchat-current-user.\\\" I want to make it clear, so users understand the significance of using descriptive names for better organization. It's important to keep things straightforward while providing clear examples!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] The folder name is based on the **user identifier** passed into the logging script, after a small sanitization step.\n\n### Current logic\nFor each record, the script uses:\n\n- `user_id` → becomes the folder name\n- invalid/path-unsafe characters → replaced with `_`\n- leading/trailing `.`, `_`, `-` → trimmed\n- if nothing usable remains → fallback to `unknown-user`\n\nSo for the tests I ran:\n- `sample-user-123` → `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data/sample-user-123/`\n- `webchat-current-user` → `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data/webchat-current-user/`\n\n### Why you see “sample” folders\nThose were created during my test runs to validate:\n- new file creation\n- update/merge behavior\n- deduplication\n\nThey are not special system folders — just test user IDs I used.\n\n### Important design note\nRight now, the naming logic is only as good as the `user_id` we provide. So in production, we should use a **stable real identifier** from the chat/session/provider context, for example:\n- provider user ID\n- phone number hash\n- platform account ID\n- internal patient ID\n\nThat way, the same person always maps to the same folder.\n\nIf you want, I can do either of these next:\n1. **delete the sample test folders**, or  \n2. **improve the logic** so the agent derives a more realistic/stable per-user folder name automatically.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a89ffc288191a9681d04a9ccbf72\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1392,"output":359,"cacheRead":30080,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31831,"cost":{"input":0.0034800000000000005,"output":0.005385,"cacheRead":0.00752,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.016385}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773250715358}}
