{"type":"message","id":"c74ee3b3","parentId":"07a3f090","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:41:11.937Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating skill application**\n\nI’m considering if I need to apply the skill creator with the already loaded data. I’ve checked that I’ve already read the skill, so I just need to respond affirmatively. I might need to modify the existing skill by adding a script and then update it accordingly. Once that’s done, I could test it out and package everything. It feels like there’s a lot to keep track of, but I think I can manage it!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a91339a0819190aaa72e027ca2a4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpsakWgYR0rZkCd5q0ycIK1wwP3u8KQCbFcj-Pw3WXXA4ElevpNfy_csRY6kUrSM8fWvNimRzXVBXt8H8fWHruWJrXLZIAaa_d2QJrJOVPsrViqiF7zAoUETYCvU6Zqiltc1NoIZIzkzAGqfGP2ifRFzqDdZsGmI-iDILUbw2jCcyQK3Spg8M7UNiv_HkuttFkDKimVLe2wi4luu9PySKY0CpgU0zLEgGIDIFKbBpTn3S6xA7k8GkbE7-98-INpVHH3eS6xhVPe8bAUFVGl75Dw97MENjsJkWuhxCXzfATv2V-m5tNp54qCM6wmf8F6r-Yckcf3lMJPOwfS3Jlkzz0UsK_jmOg0i-Wz94HlTyzngZVRQIHf7bq1pR4a4uYh56KJp7QZdlt736qm1wdij6MlB5GqAbRVHtzwNcZSvmcrqmIkh8k4N1BbX9OKkB8GSG_x77J1P9cO7r4gHGjVthfMKF-VxPPDAkwVzCtbYZ-telQAAGg2o90PwCRanPAaM5NXKjoKgCKSVhLQKkHqpyPVPzDvIXGh76UJ-ZHh8F7UU-qYXLlm9R368YSXzXMG-hyHr0ae0O-Yp5fGQLTQQg7OtXAEtbGSAzji2O7Eh7AgrN9mzqUyPOC_5iZgMrivzZ4JsHhB22Z5914lYXFUO6RA1xOI13o4YTGwF3kgjT_OBzJhXdMZMm39xx8QlZd093nrNG3oUXswO0F0YhBXweUaFjONYvc9AyCPFNxwo70p_KRjjj36XNid69pK3LFfzJRrEnwh77qAUnobZebDV0aKCiOJj7DL0-8ge5WDoMy6uATAqxUPdgapSz6tLC4HbIlZ8j-ltFVFzkTxMj7Vcy0delKJAC9IMAyKaasQAKTyn_YoJGkHdsMaFJyJ1HP_t_5NKB8SvnE2p9DJvoEqhMgokxV8RoG5aeZNUrcrn3R4RLjdj2sgaSQbf_IHEgOtmaEaLGNeMXfDA3ZAjk2QIGhMGvgwI0s2hdV6EsxbZdIhrsa430VNpTrrukIRbLAcVPe4F5bSYfqjbyI6FoBoOOsu2wjNGWUNuN1ihyIX3k5fViWp88=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating skill application**\\n\\nI’m considering if I need to apply the skill creator with the already loaded data. I’ve checked that I’ve already read the skill, so I just need to respond affirmatively. I might need to modify the existing skill by adding a script and then update it accordingly. Once that’s done, I could test it out and package everything. It feels like there’s a lot to keep track of, but I think I can manage it!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Yes — that’s a good fit for the same skill. I’ll add a companion read/summarize script that loads a user’s JSON record and returns a concise structured summary, then I’ll validate it and repackage the skill.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a91686188191b0ba03ae21c6bbbb\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0n4raF2L5NKio7lIrxhtZoXz|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a937d0c48191a980fc10874e5d7f","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/scripts/summarize_user_medical_data.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List\n\nBASE_DIR = Path('/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data')\n\n\ndef slugify_user_id(user_id: str) -> str:\n    cleaned = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9._-]+', '_', user_id.strip())\n    cleaned = cleaned.strip('._-')\n    return cleaned or 'unknown-user'\n\n\ndef load_record(user_id: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    record_path = BASE_DIR / slugify_user_id(user_id) / 'medical_data.json'\n    if not record_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f'No medical data found for user_id={user_id} at {record_path}')\n    with record_path.open('r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        data = json.load(f)\n    data['_record_path'] = str(record_path)\n    return data\n\n\ndef nonempty_basic_fields(basic: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    result = {}\n    for key, value in (basic or {}).items():\n        if value is None:\n            continue\n        if isinstance(value, str) and not value.strip():\n            continue\n        if isinstance(value, list) and not value:\n            continue\n        result[key] = value\n    return result\n\n\ndef latest_entries(timeline: List[Dict[str, Any]], limit: int) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n    sorted_items = sorted(\n        timeline or [],\n        key=lambda x: (x.get('timestamp') or '', x.get('type') or '', x.get('text') or ''),\n        reverse=True,\n    )\n    return sorted_items[:limit]\n\n\ndef build_summary(data: Dict[str, Any], recent_limit: int) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    basic = nonempty_basic_fields(data.get('basic_health_data', {}))\n    timeline = data.get('symptom_health_timeline', [])\n    recent = latest_entries(timeline, recent_limit)\n\n    symptom_count = sum(1 for item in timeline if item.get('type') == 'symptom')\n    measurement_count = sum(1 for item in timeline if item.get('type') == 'measurement')\n\n    return {\n        'user_id': data.get('user_id'),\n        'record_path': data.get('_record_path'),\n        'created_at': data.get('created_at'),\n        'updated_at': data.get('updated_at'),\n        'basic_health_data': basic,\n        'timeline_entry_count': len(timeline),\n        'symptom_entry_count': symptom_count,\n        'measurement_entry_count': measurement_count,\n        'recent_timeline_entries': recent,\n    }\n\n\ndef print_human_summary(summary: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n    print(f\"User ID: {summary.get('user_id')}\")\n    print(f\"Record: {summary.get('record_path')}\")\n    print(f\"Created: {summary.get('created_at')}\")\n    print(f\"Updated: {summary.get('updated_at')}\")\n    print('')\n    print('Basic health data:')\n    basic = summary.get('basic_health_data') or {}\n    if not basic:\n        print('- None recorded')\n    else:\n        for key, value in basic.items():\n            print(f'- {key}: {value}')\n    print('')\n    print(f\"Timeline entries: {summary.get('timeline_entry_count', 0)}\")\n    print(f\"Symptoms logged: {summary.get('symptom_entry_count', 0)}\")\n    print(f\"Measurements logged: {summary.get('measurement_entry_count', 0)}\")\n    print('')\n    print('Recent timeline entries:')\n    recent = summary.get('recent_timeline_entries') or []\n    if not recent:\n        print('- None recorded')\n    else:\n        for item in recent:\n            print(f\"- [{item.get('timestamp')}] {item.get('type')}: {item.get('text')}\")\n\n\ndef main() -> int:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='Summarize structured user medical data records.')\n    parser.add_argument('--user-id', required=True, help='Stable user identifier')\n    parser.add_argument('--recent-limit', type=int, default=10, help='Number of recent timeline entries to show')\n    parser.add_argument('--format', choices=['text', 'json'], default='text', help='Output format')\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    data = load_record(args.user_id)\n    summary = build_summary(data, args.recent_limit)\n\n    if args.format == 'json':\n        print(json.dumps(summary, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False))\n    else:\n        print_human_summary(summary)\n    return 0\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    raise SystemExit(main())\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/scripts/summarize_user_medical_data.py\",\"content\":\"#!/usr/bin/env python3\\nimport argparse\\nimport json\\nimport re\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List\\n\\nBASE_DIR = Path('/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data')\\n\\n\\ndef slugify_user_id(user_id: str) -> str:\\n    cleaned = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9._-]+', '_', user_id.strip())\\n    cleaned = cleaned.strip('._-')\\n    return cleaned or 'unknown-user'\\n\\n\\ndef load_record(user_id: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\\n    record_path = BASE_DIR / slugify_user_id(user_id) / 'medical_data.json'\\n    if not record_path.exists():\\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f'No medical data found for user_id={user_id} at {record_path}')\\n    with record_path.open('r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\\n        data = json.load(f)\\n    data['_record_path'] = str(record_path)\\n    return data\\n\\n\\ndef nonempty_basic_fields(basic: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]:\\n    result = {}\\n    for key, value in (basic or {}).items():\\n        if value is None:\\n            continue\\n        if isinstance(value, str) and not value.strip():\\n            continue\\n        if isinstance(value, list) and not value:\\n            continue\\n        result[key] = value\\n    return result\\n\\n\\ndef latest_entries(timeline: List[Dict[str, Any]], limit: int) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\\n    sorted_items = sorted(\\n        timeline or [],\\n        key=lambda x: (x.get('timestamp') or '', x.get('type') or '', x.get('text') or ''),\\n        reverse=True,\\n    )\\n    return sorted_items[:limit]\\n\\n\\ndef build_summary(data: Dict[str, Any], recent_limit: int) -> Dict[str, Any]:\\n    basic = nonempty_basic_fields(data.get('basic_health_data', {}))\\n    timeline = data.get('symptom_health_timeline', [])\\n    recent = latest_entries(timeline, recent_limit)\\n\\n    symptom_count = sum(1 for item in timeline if item.get('type') == 'symptom')\\n    measurement_count = sum(1 for item in timeline if item.get('type') == 'measurement')\\n\\n    return {\\n        'user_id': data.get('user_id'),\\n        'record_path': data.get('_record_path'),\\n        'created_at': data.get('created_at'),\\n        'updated_at': data.get('updated_at'),\\n        'basic_health_data': basic,\\n        'timeline_entry_count': len(timeline),\\n        'symptom_entry_count': symptom_count,\\n        'measurement_entry_count': measurement_count,\\n        'recent_timeline_entries': recent,\\n    }\\n\\n\\ndef print_human_summary(summary: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\\n    print(f\\\"User ID: {summary.get('user_id')}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Record: {summary.get('record_path')}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Created: {summary.get('created_at')}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Updated: {summary.get('updated_at')}\\\")\\n    print('')\\n    print('Basic health data:')\\n    basic = summary.get('basic_health_data') or {}\\n    if not basic:\\n        print('- None recorded')\\n    else:\\n        for key, value in basic.items():\\n            print(f'- {key}: {value}')\\n    print('')\\n    print(f\\\"Timeline entries: {summary.get('timeline_entry_count', 0)}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Symptoms logged: {summary.get('symptom_entry_count', 0)}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"Measurements logged: {summary.get('measurement_entry_count', 0)}\\\")\\n    print('')\\n    print('Recent timeline entries:')\\n    recent = summary.get('recent_timeline_entries') or []\\n    if not recent:\\n        print('- None recorded')\\n    else:\\n        for item in recent:\\n            print(f\\\"- [{item.get('timestamp')}] {item.get('type')}: {item.get('text')}\\\")\\n\\n\\ndef main() -> int:\\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description='Summarize structured user medical data records.')\\n    parser.add_argument('--user-id', required=True, help='Stable user identifier')\\n    parser.add_argument('--recent-limit', type=int, default=10, help='Number of recent timeline entries to show')\\n    parser.add_argument('--format', choices=['text', 'json'], default='text', help='Output format')\\n    args = parser.parse_args()\\n\\n    data = load_record(args.user_id)\\n    summary = build_summary(data, args.recent_limit)\\n\\n    if args.format == 'json':\\n        print(json.dumps(summary, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False))\\n    else:\\n        print_human_summary(summary)\\n    return 0\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    raise SystemExit(main())\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_DK7PN8y1Gg9CTqaLo1l5xltd|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a937d0dc8191b3e25c171633ef53","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/references/schema.md","content":"# User Medical Data Record Schema\n\n## Storage location\n\nStore each user's data at:\n\n- `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data/<sanitized-user-id>/medical_data.json`\n\nThe folder name should be a sanitized form of the user identifier.\n\n## Record structure\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schema_version\": \"1.0\",\n  \"user_id\": \"example-user\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-11T17:00:00Z\",\n  \"updated_at\": \"2026-03-11T17:05:00Z\",\n  \"basic_health_data\": {\n    \"full_name\": null,\n    \"preferred_name\": null,\n    \"date_of_birth\": null,\n    \"age\": null,\n    \"sex\": null,\n    \"gender\": null,\n    \"blood_type\": null,\n    \"height_cm\": null,\n    \"weight_kg\": null,\n    \"allergies\": [],\n    \"chronic_conditions\": [],\n    \"medications\": [],\n    \"emergency_contact\": null,\n    \"primary_physician\": null,\n    \"notes\": null\n  },\n  \"symptom_health_timeline\": [\n    {\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-11T17:04:00Z\",\n      \"type\": \"symptom\",\n      \"text\": \"Headache for the last 2 days\",\n      \"source\": \"user_report\",\n      \"status\": \"reported\",\n      \"metadata\": {}\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Merge rules\n\n- Create the record if it does not exist.\n- Preserve existing content unless the new payload intentionally updates it.\n- For scalar `basic_health_data` fields, overwrite only when the new value is non-empty.\n- For list `basic_health_data` fields, merge unique values.\n- For `symptom_health_timeline`, append non-empty new entries and skip exact duplicates.\n- Keep timestamps in ISO-8601 UTC form when possible.\n- Sort the timeline by timestamp after merging.\n\n## Summary behavior\n\nThe companion summary script reads one user record and returns:\n- record metadata (`user_id`, path, timestamps)\n- only non-empty `basic_health_data` fields\n- total timeline entry count\n- symptom and measurement counts\n- a recent slice of timeline entries\n\n## Recommended timeline entry types\n\n- `symptom`\n- `health_note`\n- `measurement`\n- `diagnosis_history`\n- `medication_update`\n\n## Minimal payload example\n\n```json\n{\n  \"user_id\": \"example-user\",\n  \"basic_health_data\": {\n    \"age\": 42,\n    \"blood_type\": \"O+\"\n  },\n  \"symptom_health_timeline\": [\n    {\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-11T17:04:00Z\",\n      \"type\": \"symptom\",\n      \"text\": \"Low-grade fever since yesterday\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/references/schema.md\",\"content\":\"# User Medical Data Record Schema\\n\\n## Storage location\\n\\nStore each user's data at:\\n\\n- `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data/<sanitized-user-id>/medical_data.json`\\n\\nThe folder name should be a sanitized form of the user identifier.\\n\\n## Record structure\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"schema_version\\\": \\\"1.0\\\",\\n  \\\"user_id\\\": \\\"example-user\\\",\\n  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-03-11T17:00:00Z\\\",\\n  \\\"updated_at\\\": \\\"2026-03-11T17:05:00Z\\\",\\n  \\\"basic_health_data\\\": {\\n    \\\"full_name\\\": null,\\n    \\\"preferred_name\\\": null,\\n    \\\"date_of_birth\\\": null,\\n    \\\"age\\\": null,\\n    \\\"sex\\\": null,\\n    \\\"gender\\\": null,\\n    \\\"blood_type\\\": null,\\n    \\\"height_cm\\\": null,\\n    \\\"weight_kg\\\": null,\\n    \\\"allergies\\\": [],\\n    \\\"chronic_conditions\\\": [],\\n    \\\"medications\\\": [],\\n    \\\"emergency_contact\\\": null,\\n    \\\"primary_physician\\\": null,\\n    \\\"notes\\\": null\\n  },\\n  \\\"symptom_health_timeline\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-03-11T17:04:00Z\\\",\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"symptom\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Headache for the last 2 days\\\",\\n      \\\"source\\\": \\\"user_report\\\",\\n      \\\"status\\\": \\\"reported\\\",\\n      \\\"metadata\\\": {}\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Merge rules\\n\\n- Create the record if it does not exist.\\n- Preserve existing content unless the new payload intentionally updates it.\\n- For scalar `basic_health_data` fields, overwrite only when the new value is non-empty.\\n- For list `basic_health_data` fields, merge unique values.\\n- For `symptom_health_timeline`, append non-empty new entries and skip exact duplicates.\\n- Keep timestamps in ISO-8601 UTC form when possible.\\n- Sort the timeline by timestamp after merging.\\n\\n## Summary behavior\\n\\nThe companion summary script reads one user record and returns:\\n- record metadata (`user_id`, path, timestamps)\\n- only non-empty `basic_health_data` fields\\n- total timeline entry count\\n- symptom and measurement counts\\n- a recent slice of timeline entries\\n\\n## Recommended timeline entry types\\n\\n- `symptom`\\n- `health_note`\\n- `measurement`\\n- `diagnosis_history`\\n- `medication_update`\\n\\n## Minimal payload example\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"user_id\\\": \\\"example-user\\\",\\n  \\\"basic_health_data\\\": {\\n    \\\"age\\\": 42,\\n    \\\"blood_type\\\": \\\"O+\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"symptom_health_timeline\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-03-11T17:04:00Z\\\",\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"symptom\\\",\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Low-grade fever since yesterday\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":565,"output":2030,"cacheRead":31360,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33955,"cost":{"input":0.0014125000000000001,"output":0.03045,"cacheRead":0.00784,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0397025}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773250833985}}
