{"type":"message","id":"209e6f9f","parentId":"3a7d998b","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:41:48.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Done — I added the **summary/readback feature** into the same skill and verified it works.\n\n### What was added\nNew script:\n\n- `/home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/scripts/summarize_user_medical_data.py`\n\nUpdated skill package:\n\n- `/home/node/.openclaw/skills/dist/user-medical-data-update.skill`\n\n### What it does\nGiven a user ID, it reads that user’s:\n\n- `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data/<user-id>/medical_data.json`\n\nand returns a summary including:\n\n- user ID\n- record path\n- created/updated timestamps\n- only the **non-empty** basic health fields\n- total timeline entry count\n- symptom count\n- measurement count\n- recent timeline entries\n\n### Usage\nText summary:\n\n```bash\npython3 /home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/scripts/summarize_user_medical_data.py --user-id webchat-current-user\n```\n\nJSON summary:\n\n```bash\npython3 /home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/scripts/summarize_user_medical_data.py --user-id webchat-current-user --format json\n```\n\nLimit recent entries:\n\n```bash\npython3 /home/node/.openclaw/skills/user-medical-data-update/scripts/summarize_user_medical_data.py --user-id webchat-current-user --recent-limit 5\n```\n\n### Tested result\nI tested it against the record created from your earlier symptoms, and it correctly summarized:\n- age: 28\n- 3 total timeline entries\n- 2 symptom entries\n- recent items including headache, red eyes, and poor sleep\n\nIf you want, I can now do the next useful step: make the agent **automatically call this summary capability when the user asks things like “summarize my medical data” or “what do you know about my symptoms so far?”**","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1a9550b3c8191b086726f4a4fd167\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"