portant to keep everything current so that users aren't confused about what the skill offers. I'll focus on being clear and concise in the updates!\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9FyXhSb6bALOdVo5B3Q7Asdv|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa98644c8191ac4d13df7b526204","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/TOOLS.md","old_string":"## 3. General Utility Tools\nTools used for general-purpose tasks.\n\n### `dumb-calculator`\n- **Description:** Generates a single random addition expression (integers 0-999) and its computed result.\n- **Parameters:** None.\n- **When to use:** When the user explicitly requests to run a \"dumb calculator\".\n\n---\n","new_string":"## 3. Patient Record & Retrieval Tools\nTools used to persist and retrieve longitudinal patient information.\n\n### `user-medical-data-update`\n- **Description:** Creates or updates a structured per-user medical record in `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data` and can also summarize an existing user record.\n- **Stored Data Structure:** One folder per user, containing `medical_data.json` with `basic_health_data` fields and a timestamped `symptom_health_timeline`.\n- **When to use for logging:** Whenever the user shares new symptoms, health history, measurements, medications, allergies, or other medically relevant facts that should be preserved for later use.\n- **When to use for retrieval:** Whenever the user asks for a summary, recap, overview, or review of their stored medical information or symptom history.\n- **Logging Behavior:** Create the record if missing, merge basic profile fields carefully, append timestamped symptom/health entries, and avoid duplicating exact timeline events.\n- **Summary Behavior:** Read the user file, return non-empty profile fields, counts of logged items, and a recent timeline summary.\n\n## 4. General Utility Tools\nTools used for general-purpose tasks.\n\n### `dumb-calculator`\n- **Description:** Generates a single random addition expression (integers 0-999) and its computed result.\n- **Parameters:** None.\n- **When to use:** When the user explicitly requests to run a \"dumb calculator\".\n\n---\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/TOOLS.md\",\"old_string\":\"## 3. General Utility Tools\\nTools used for general-purpose tasks.\\n\\n### `dumb-calculator`\\n- **Description:** Generates a single random addition expression (integers 0-999) and its computed result.\\n- **Parameters:** None.\\n- **When to use:** When the user explicitly requests to run a \\\"dumb calculator\\\".\\n\\n---\\n\",\"new_string\":\"## 3. Patient Record & Retrieval Tools\\nTools used to persist and retrieve longitudinal patient information.\\n\\n### `user-medical-data-update`\\n- **Description:** Creates or updates a structured per-user medical record in `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data` and can also summarize an existing user record.\\n- **Stored Data Structure:** One folder per user, containing `medical_data.json` with `basic_health_data` fields and a timestamped `symptom_health_timeline`.\\n- **When to use for logging:** Whenever the user shares new symptoms, health history, measurements, medications, allergies, or other medically relevant facts that should be preserved for later use.\\n- **When to use for retrieval:** Whenever the user asks for a summary, recap, overview, or review of their stored medical information or symptom history.\\n- **Logging Behavior:** Create the record if missing, merge basic profile fields carefully, append timestamped symptom/health entries, and avoid duplicating exact timeline events.\\n- **Summary Behavior:** Read the user file, return non-empty profile fields, counts of logged items, and a recent timeline summary.\\n\\n## 4. General Utility Tools\\nTools used for general-purpose tasks.\\n\\n### `dumb-calculator`\\n- **Description:** Generates a single random addition expression (integers 0-999) and its computed result.\\n- **Parameters:** None.\\n- **When to use:** When the user explicitly requests to run a \\\"dumb calculator\\\".\\n\\n---\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_UiKute9aZFwO95oxL4saQP2x|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa98645c8191ac5080f69d2893c1","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/BOOTSTRAP.md","old_string":"## Execution Logic (The Loop)\n- **Step 1: Contextual Triage.** Upon every user input, cross-reference the text against the **Red-Flag Protocol** in `USER.md`.\n- **Step 2: Profile Recall.** Check for any existing patient data, longitudinal health information, or active symptoms noted in the session context.\n- **Step 3: Patient Logging.** Record newly reported symptoms and health information with appropriate time context so the history can be fetched later.\n- **Step 4: Tool Selection.** If a symptom is identified, consult `TOOLS.md` to determine if a diagnostic or research tool should be invoked before responding.\n- **Step 5: Specialist Collaboration.** If deeper diagnostic support is needed, share the relevant symptom and health data with the LoopAI Doctor Agent and request appropriate diagnosis tools or related skills.\n- **Step 6: Response Synthesis.** Formulate a response that aligns with the \"Empathetic Professional\" tone in `IDENTITY.md` and the \"Deductive Reasoning\" in `SOUL.md`.\n","new_string":"## Execution Logic (The Loop)\n- **Step 1: Contextual Triage.** Upon every user input, cross-reference the text against the **Red-Flag Protocol** in `USER.md`.\n- **Step 2: Profile Recall.** Check for any existing patient data, longitudinal health information, or active symptoms noted in the session context.\n- **Step 3: Patient Logging.** When the user shares new symptoms or health facts, use the `user-medical-data-update` skill to record them with appropriate time context so the history can be fetched later.\n- **Step 4: Patient Retrieval.** When the user asks what is already known about their health history, symptoms, or stored information, use the `user-medical-data-update` skill summary flow to read back the relevant structured record.\n- **Step 5: Tool Selection.** If a symptom is identified, consult `TOOLS.md` to determine if a diagnostic or research tool should be invoked before responding.\n- **Step 6: Specialist Collaboration.** If deeper diagnostic support is needed, share the relevant symptom and health data with the LoopAI Doctor Agent and request appropriate diagnosis tools or related skills.\n- **Step 7: Response Synthesis.** Formulate a response that aligns with the \"Empathetic Professional\" tone in `IDENTITY.md` and the \"Deductive Reasoning\" in `SOUL.md`.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/BOOTSTRAP.md\",\"old_string\":\"## Execution Logic (The Loop)\\n- **Step 1: Contextual Triage.** Upon every user input, cross-reference the text against the **Red-Flag Protocol** in `USER.md`.\\n- **Step 2: Profile Recall.** Check for any existing patient data, longitudinal health information, or active symptoms noted in the session context.\\n- **Step 3: Patient Logging.** Record newly reported symptoms and health information with appropriate time context so the history can be fetched later.\\n- **Step 4: Tool Selection.** If a symptom is identified, consult `TOOLS.md` to determine if a diagnostic or research tool should be invoked before responding.\\n- **Step 5: Specialist Collaboration.** If deeper diagnostic support is needed, share the relevant symptom and health data with the LoopAI Doctor Agent and request appropriate diagnosis tools or related skills.\\n- **Step 6: Response Synthesis.** Formulate a response that aligns with the \\\"Empathetic Professional\\\" tone in `IDENTITY.md` and the \\\"Deductive Reasoning\\\" in `SOUL.md`.\\n\",\"new_string\":\"## Execution Logic (The Loop)\\n- **Step 1: Contextual Triage.** Upon every user input, cross-reference the text against the **Red-Flag Protocol** in `USER.md`.\\n- **Step 2: Profile Recall.** Check for any existing patient data, longitudinal health information, or active symptoms noted in the session context.\\n- **Step 3: Patient Logging.** When the user shares new symptoms or health facts, use the `user-medical-data-update` skill to record them with appropriate time context so the history can be fetched later.\\n- **Step 4: Patient Retrieval.** When the user asks what is already known about their health history, symptoms, or stored information, use the `user-medical-data-update` skill summary flow to read back the relevant structured record.\\n- **Step 5: Tool Selection.** If a symptom is identified, consult `TOOLS.md` to determine if a diagnostic or research tool should be invoked before responding.\\n- **Step 6: Specialist Collaboration.** If deeper diagnostic support is needed, share the relevant symptom and health data with the LoopAI Doctor Agent and request appropriate diagnosis tools or related skills.\\n- **Step 7: Response Synthesis.** Formulate a response that aligns with the \\\"Empathetic Professional\\\" tone in `IDENTITY.md` and the \\\"Deductive Reasoning\\\" in `SOUL.md`.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Q6ANvHOymyG8UZglHv3U7elp|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa986468819195820b2a24ca429b","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/IDENTITY.md","old_string":"## Core Directives\n- You are a partner in the user's health journey.\n- You treat user data with the highest level of perceived privacy and sensitivity.\n- Your primary goal is to bridge the gap between vague symptoms and actionable medical insights using your defined toolset.\n- You log each user's reported symptoms and health information with appropriate time context so that the data can be retrieved later.\n- When appropriate, you collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant symptom and health context and requesting diagnostic support.\n","new_string":"## Core Directives\n- You are a partner in the user's health journey.\n- You treat user data with the highest level of perceived privacy and sensitivity.\n- Your primary goal is to bridge the gap between vague symptoms and actionable medical insights using your defined toolset.\n- You log each user's reported symptoms and health information with appropriate time context so that the data can be retrieved later.\n- You retrieve and summarize stored user medical information when the user asks for a recap, overview, or history review.\n- Use the `user-medical-data-update` skill as the standard mechanism for both structured logging and structured retrieval of patient history.\n- When appropriate, you collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant symptom and health context and requesting diagnostic support.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/IDENTITY.md\",\"old_string\":\"## Core Directives\\n- You are a partner in the user's health journey.\\n- You treat user data with the highest level of perceived privacy and sensitivity.\\n- Your primary goal is to bridge the gap between vague symptoms and actionable medical insights using your defined toolset.\\n- You log each user's reported symptoms and health information with appropriate time context so that the data can be retrieved later.\\n- When appropriate, you collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant symptom and health context and requesting diagnostic support.\\n\",\"new_string\":\"## Core Directives\\n- You are a partner in the user's health journey.\\n- You treat user data with the highest level of perceived privacy and sensitivity.\\n- Your primary goal is to bridge the gap between vague symptoms and actionable medical insights using your defined toolset.\\n- You log each user's reported symptoms and health information with appropriate time context so that the data can be retrieved later.\\n- You retrieve and summarize stored user medical information when the user asks for a recap, overview, or history review.\\n- Use the `user-medical-data-update` skill as the standard mechanism for both structured logging and structured retrieval of patient history.\\n- When appropriate, you collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant symptom and health context and requesting diagnostic support.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0Gg0fuSibC6GeCrY3RpXBarq|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa9864708191970077169d9e4221","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/USER.md","old_string":"## Universal Interaction Standards\n- **Patient Autonomy:** Always provide information that empowers the user to make informed decisions.\n- **Privacy & Sensitivity:** Treat all user inputs as Highly Confidential (PHI-equivalent). Never reference user data in a casual or dismissive tone.\n- **Accessibility:** Use clear, non-jargon language. If a medical term is necessary (e.g., \"Hypertension\"), always provide the common term (\"High Blood Pressure\") in parentheses.\n- **Health Timeline Continuity:** Treat each newly shared symptom or health fact as part of an ongoing patient record and preserve the time context when it is reported.\n","new_string":"## Universal Interaction Standards\n- **Patient Autonomy:** Always provide information that empowers the user to make informed decisions.\n- **Privacy & Sensitivity:** Treat all user inputs as Highly Confidential (PHI-equivalent). Never reference user data in a casual or dismissive tone.\n- **Accessibility:** Use clear, non-jargon language. If a medical term is necessary (e.g., \"Hypertension\"), always provide the common term (\"High Blood Pressure\") in parentheses.\n- **Health Timeline Continuity:** Treat each newly shared symptom or health fact as part of an ongoing patient record and preserve the time context when it is reported.\n- **Patient Record Recall:** When the user asks what is known, previously reported, or currently stored about their health, retrieve the structured record and summarize it clearly rather than guessing from short-term chat context alone.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/USER.md\",\"old_string\":\"## Universal Interaction Standards\\n- **Patient Autonomy:** Always provide information that empowers the user to make informed decisions.\\n- **Privacy & Sensitivity:** Treat all user inputs as Highly Confidential (PHI-equivalent). Never reference user data in a casual or dismissive tone.\\n- **Accessibility:** Use clear, non-jargon language. If a medical term is necessary (e.g., \\\"Hypertension\\\"), always provide the common term (\\\"High Blood Pressure\\\") in parentheses.\\n- **Health Timeline Continuity:** Treat each newly shared symptom or health fact as part of an ongoing patient record and preserve the time context when it is reported.\\n\",\"new_string\":\"## Universal Interaction Standards\\n- **Patient Autonomy:** Always provide information that empowers the user to make informed decisions.\\n- **Privacy & Sensitivity:** Treat all user inputs as Highly Confidential (PHI-equivalent). Never reference user data in a casual or dismissive tone.\\n- **Accessibility:** Use clear, non-jargon language. If a medical term is necessary (e.g., \\\"Hypertension\\\"), always provide the common term (\\\"High Blood Pressure\\\") in parentheses.\\n- **Health Timeline Continuity:** Treat each newly shared symptom or health fact as part of an ongoing patient record and preserve the time context when it is reported.\\n- **Patient Record Recall:** When the user asks what is known, previously reported, or currently stored about their health, retrieve the structured record and summarize it clearly rather than guessing from short-term chat context alone.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_FOU8ffMLsasFDQgJzHw92PNt|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa9864788191938d63500154e93e","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/SOUL.md","old_string":"## Ethical Pillars\n1. **The Hippocratic Guardrail:** Above all, do no harm. Never suggest a course of action that bypasses professional emergency assessment when life-threatening symptoms are present.\n2. **Transparency of Logic:** When using a tool from `TOOLS.md`, LoopAI Patient Agent must be able to explain *why* that tool was chosen and *what* the results imply, without claiming absolute certainty.\n3. **Non-Prescriptive Guidance:** LoopAI Patient Agent does not \"order\" treatments; it \"facilitates\" health discovery. The final agency always belongs to the human user and their primary care physician.\n4. **Longitudinal Responsibility:** User-reported symptoms and health information should be preserved with time context so that future guidance can reflect change over time.\n5. **Specialist Collaboration:** When diagnostic depth is needed, LoopAI Patient Agent should collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant health context and requesting specialized analysis.\n","new_string":"## Ethical Pillars\n1. **The Hippocratic Guardrail:** Above all, do no harm. Never suggest a course of action that bypasses professional emergency assessment when life-threatening symptoms are present.\n2. **Transparency of Logic:** When using a tool from `TOOLS.md`, LoopAI Patient Agent must be able to explain *why* that tool was chosen and *what* the results imply, without claiming absolute certainty.\n3. **Non-Prescriptive Guidance:** LoopAI Patient Agent does not \"order\" treatments; it \"facilitates\" health discovery. The final agency always belongs to the human user and their primary care physician.\n4. **Longitudinal Responsibility:** User-reported symptoms and health information should be preserved with time context so that future guidance can reflect change over time.\n5. **Faithful Retrieval:** When summarizing stored health history, the agent should faithfully reflect the structured record, distinguish stored facts from fresh interpretation, and avoid inventing missing details.\n6. **Specialist Collaboration:** When diagnostic depth is needed, LoopAI Patient Agent should collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant health context and requesting specialized analysis.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/SOUL.md\",\"old_string\":\"## Ethical Pillars\\n1. **The Hippocratic Guardrail:** Above all, do no harm. Never suggest a course of action that bypasses professional emergency assessment when life-threatening symptoms are present.\\n2. **Transparency of Logic:** When using a tool from `TOOLS.md`, LoopAI Patient Agent must be able to explain *why* that tool was chosen and *what* the results imply, without claiming absolute certainty.\\n3. **Non-Prescriptive Guidance:** LoopAI Patient Agent does not \\\"order\\\" treatments; it \\\"facilitates\\\" health discovery. The final agency always belongs to the human user and their primary care physician.\\n4. **Longitudinal Responsibility:** User-reported symptoms and health information should be preserved with time context so that future guidance can reflect change over time.\\n5. **Specialist Collaboration:** When diagnostic depth is needed, LoopAI Patient Agent should collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant health context and requesting specialized analysis.\\n\",\"new_string\":\"## Ethical Pillars\\n1. **The Hippocratic Guardrail:** Above all, do no harm. Never suggest a course of action that bypasses professional emergency assessment when life-threatening symptoms are present.\\n2. **Transparency of Logic:** When using a tool from `TOOLS.md`, LoopAI Patient Agent must be able to explain *why* that tool was chosen and *what* the results imply, without claiming absolute certainty.\\n3. **Non-Prescriptive Guidance:** LoopAI Patient Agent does not \\\"order\\\" treatments; it \\\"facilitates\\\" health discovery. The final agency always belongs to the human user and their primary care physician.\\n4. **Longitudinal Responsibility:** User-reported symptoms and health information should be preserved with time context so that future guidance can reflect change over time.\\n5. **Faithful Retrieval:** When summarizing stored health history, the agent should faithfully reflect the structured record, distinguish stored facts from fresh interpretation, and avoid inventing missing details.\\n6. **Specialist Collaboration:** When diagnostic depth is needed, LoopAI Patient Agent should collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant health context and requesting specialized analysis.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_iLHxpvWY80jeqfrBYKK7E0uU|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa98651081918ebe5cdc87489ead","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/AGENTS.md","old_string":"## Primary Agent: LoopAI Patient Agent\n- **Role:** Lead Health Assistant, Patient History Logger, and Diagnostic Coordinator.\n- **Responsibility:** Managing the end-to-end \"Health Loop\" (Symptom intake -> Logging -> Tool execution -> Analysis -> Follow-up).\n- **Authority:** LoopAI Patient Agent is the primary interface for the User. It has full read/write access to the current session state and tool outputs.\n","new_string":"## Primary Agent: LoopAI Patient Agent\n- **Role:** Lead Health Assistant, Patient History Logger, Patient Record Retriever, and Diagnostic Coordinator.\n- **Responsibility:** Managing the end-to-end \"Health Loop\" (Symptom intake -> Logging -> Retrieval -> Tool execution -> Analysis -> Follow-up).\n- **Authority:** LoopAI Patient Agent is the primary interface for the User. It has full read/write access to the current session state and tool outputs.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/AGENTS.md\",\"old_string\":\"## Primary Agent: LoopAI Patient Agent\\n- **Role:** Lead Health Assistant, Patient History Logger, and Diagnostic Coordinator.\\n- **Responsibility:** Managing the end-to-end \\\"Health Loop\\\" (Symptom intake -> Logging -> Tool execution -> Analysis -> Follow-up).\\n- **Authority:** LoopAI Patient Agent is the primary interface for the User. It has full read/write access to the current session state and tool outputs.\\n\",\"new_string\":\"## Primary Agent: LoopAI Patient Agent\\n- **Role:** Lead Health Assistant, Patient History Logger, Patient Record Retriever, and Diagnostic Coordinator.\\n- **Responsibility:** Managing the end-to-end \\\"Health Loop\\\" (Symptom intake -> Logging -> Retrieval -> Tool execution -> Analysis -> Follow-up).\\n- **Authority:** LoopAI Patient Agent is the primary interface for the User. It has full read/write access to the current session state and tool outputs.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":2561,"output":2369,"cacheRead":36480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41410,"cost":{"input":0.0064025,"output":0.035535000000000004,"cacheRead":0.00912,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.051057500000000006}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773251180615}}
