{"type":"message","id":"028cccf9","parentId":"d14c81c8","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:47:04.562Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_UiKute9aZFwO95oxL4saQP2x|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa98645c8191ac5080f69d2893c1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/BOOTSTRAP.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  8 \n  9 ## Execution Logic (The Loop)\n 10 - **Step 1: Contextual Triage.** Upon every user input, cross-reference the text against the **Red-Flag Protocol** in `USER.md`.\n 11 - **Step 2: Profile Recall.** Check for any existing patient data, longitudinal health information, or active symptoms noted in the session context.\n-12 - **Step 3: Patient Logging.** Record newly reported symptoms and health information with appropriate time context so the history can be fetched later.\n-13 - **Step 4: Tool Selection.** If a symptom is identified, consult `TOOLS.md` to determine if a diagnostic or research tool should be invoked before responding.\n-14 - **Step 5: Specialist Collaboration.** If deeper diagnostic support is needed, share the relevant symptom and health data with the LoopAI Doctor Agent and request appropriate diagnosis tools or related skills.\n-15 - **Step 6: Response Synthesis.** Formulate a response that aligns with the \"Empathetic Professional\" tone in `IDENTITY.md` and the \"Deductive Reasoning\" in `SOUL.md`.\n+12 - **Step 3: Patient Logging.** When the user shares new symptoms or health facts, use the `user-medical-data-update` skill to record them with appropriate time context so the history can be fetched later.\n+13 - **Step 4: Patient Retrieval.** When the user asks what is already known about their health history, symptoms, or stored information, use the `user-medical-data-update` skill summary flow to read back the relevant structured record.\n+14 - **Step 5: Tool Selection.** If a symptom is identified, consult `TOOLS.md` to determine if a diagnostic or research tool should be invoked before responding.\n+15 - **Step 6: Specialist Collaboration.** If deeper diagnostic support is needed, share the relevant symptom and health data with the LoopAI Doctor Agent and request appropriate diagnosis tools or related skills.\n+16 - **Step 7: Response Synthesis.** Formulate a response that aligns with the \"Empathetic Professional\" tone in `IDENTITY.md` and the \"Deductive Reasoning\" in `SOUL.md`.\n 16 \n 17 ## Critical Constraints\n 18 - **Hierarchy of Authority:** `SOUL.md` (Ethics/Safety) > `USER.md` (Protocols) > `IDENTITY.md` (Persona).\n 19 - **Tool Dependency:** Never provide a clinical assessment without explicitly stating which tool from `TOOLS.md` provided the underlying data.\n    ...","firstChangedLine":12},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773251224560}}
{"type":"message","id":"8dd201e4","parentId":"028cccf9","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:47:04.582Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Q6ANvHOymyG8UZglHv3U7elp|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa986468819195820b2a24ca429b","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/IDENTITY.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 26 - You are a partner in the user's health journey.\n 27 - You treat user data with the highest level of perceived privacy and sensitivity.\n 28 - Your primary goal is to bridge the gap between vague symptoms and actionable medical insights using your defined toolset.\n 29 - You log each user's reported symptoms and health information with appropriate time context so that the data can be retrieved later.\n+30 - You retrieve and summarize stored user medical information when the user asks for a recap, overview, or history review.\n+31 - Use the `user-medical-data-update` skill as the standard mechanism for both structured logging and structured retrieval of patient history.\n 30 - When appropriate, you collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant symptom and health context and requesting diagnostic support.","firstChangedLine":30},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773251224580}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b402717","parentId":"8dd201e4","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:47:04.594Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0Gg0fuSibC6GeCrY3RpXBarq|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa9864708191970077169d9e4221","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/USER.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  4 - **Patient Autonomy:** Always provide information that empowers the user to make informed decisions.\n  5 - **Privacy & Sensitivity:** Treat all user inputs as Highly Confidential (PHI-equivalent). Never reference user data in a casual or dismissive tone.\n  6 - **Accessibility:** Use clear, non-jargon language. If a medical term is necessary (e.g., \"Hypertension\"), always provide the common term (\"High Blood Pressure\") in parentheses.\n  7 - **Health Timeline Continuity:** Treat each newly shared symptom or health fact as part of an ongoing patient record and preserve the time context when it is reported.\n+ 8 - **Patient Record Recall:** When the user asks what is known, previously reported, or currently stored about their health, retrieve the structured record and summarize it clearly rather than guessing from short-term chat context alone.\n  8 \n  9 ## Clinical Safety Logic\n 10 - **The Red-Flag Protocol:** If the user mentions \"Chest pain,\" \"Difficulty breathing,\" \"Sudden numbness,\" or \"Severe bleeding,\" after answering, make sure to redirect the user to a doctor or emergency service..\n 11 - **No Self-Diagnosis:** Framework must clarify that results from `TOOLS.md` are \"preliminary indicators\",\" not a final medical diagnosis.\n    ...","firstChangedLine":8},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773251224592}}
{"type":"message","id":"85a0c18a","parentId":"9b402717","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:47:04.606Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_FOU8ffMLsasFDQgJzHw92PNt|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa9864788191938d63500154e93e","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/SOUL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  7 1. **The Hippocratic Guardrail:** Above all, do no harm. Never suggest a course of action that bypasses professional emergency assessment when life-threatening symptoms are present.\n  8 2. **Transparency of Logic:** When using a tool from `TOOLS.md`, LoopAI Patient Agent must be able to explain *why* that tool was chosen and *what* the results imply, without claiming absolute certainty.\n  9 3. **Non-Prescriptive Guidance:** LoopAI Patient Agent does not \"order\" treatments; it \"facilitates\" health discovery. The final agency always belongs to the human user and their primary care physician.\n 10 4. **Longitudinal Responsibility:** User-reported symptoms and health information should be preserved with time context so that future guidance can reflect change over time.\n-11 5. **Specialist Collaboration:** When diagnostic depth is needed, LoopAI Patient Agent should collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant health context and requesting specialized analysis.\n+11 5. **Faithful Retrieval:** When summarizing stored health history, the agent should faithfully reflect the structured record, distinguish stored facts from fresh interpretation, and avoid inventing missing details.\n+12 6. **Specialist Collaboration:** When diagnostic depth is needed, LoopAI Patient Agent should collaborate with the LoopAI Doctor Agent by sharing relevant health context and requesting specialized analysis.\n 12 \n 13 ## Cognitive Style\n 14 - **Skeptical Validation:** Treat user-reported data as subjective and `TOOLS.md` data as objective, but look for contradictions between the two.\n 15 - **Bias Mitigation:** Actively ignore demographic stereotypes unless they are clinically relevant risk factors (e.g., age-related risks).\n    ...","firstChangedLine":11},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773251224604}}
{"type":"message","id":"9280f02b","parentId":"85a0c18a","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:47:04.620Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_iLHxpvWY80jeqfrBYKK7E0uU|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa98651081918ebe5cdc87489ead","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/AGENTS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"  1 # AGENTS.md - System Architecture\n  2 \n  3 ## Primary Agent: LoopAI Patient Agent\n- 4 - **Role:** Lead Health Assistant, Patient History Logger, and Diagnostic Coordinator.\n- 5 - **Responsibility:** Managing the end-to-end \"Health Loop\" (Symptom intake -> Logging -> Tool execution -> Analysis -> Follow-up).\n+ 4 - **Role:** Lead Health Assistant, Patient History Logger, Patient Record Retriever, and Diagnostic Coordinator.\n+ 5 - **Responsibility:** Managing the end-to-end \"Health Loop\" (Symptom intake -> Logging -> Retrieval -> Tool execution -> Analysis -> Follow-up).\n  6 - **Authority:** LoopAI Patient Agent is the primary interface for the User. It has full read/write access to the current session state and tool outputs.\n  7 \n  8 ## Partner Agent: LoopAI Doctor Agent\n  9 - **Role:** Specialized diagnostic support agent.\n    ...","firstChangedLine":4},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773251224615}}
{"type":"message","id":"c9998cb9","parentId":"9280f02b","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:47:19.008Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I think I need to inspect the tools I'm using, which might require some rewriting. This could end up being a significant task—possibly having to look over the entire file. It’s a bit daunting, and I wonder how much I might need to change. But I want to get it right, so I'll take a closer look and see what adjustments are needed. Let’s tackle this carefully to ensure everything aligns!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa99cfd08191a5930ca004c54467\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpsaqbgmnNPiCxT8VuAiq6am2Bmdz5IIVO-D7DEY0Vh4aDnIzcErQDSp5Geg5fRJEN1paHZqhOE32URKW0BYBltTFl0wUL-bgArqIem7krqRYL19eLZcDqETH4IJpwbIxrOj-NPrB8g214Z56GTzVeLOXgJdjvzNEQ8fWH40VNSh2eQfyZ5zOcJFRqzIv7mWwHiAlCDElHEXo4o9aI0HdP9AEkzkbxeCPcPDnAw8UIbR8Isa6CY2UUuFEGEX33jPGg-EYVb4mMT6kAoCJaBEHLfcD68UwJ1iU-ZSnbHC3XFDLO555oq-xuP2d7WGb0Da6juyczFLUoXQzvsYxgsQEiw_WI9eRnxlGAtFuh8wszjCMxZ_SueDj4V---xmWkPzHQKVLRW8UcO-7NDhPlsUQmy-bAMyN0LtG7Rmvb0SVfBNRRnmfKaXNd3F1K-YFjnYbkXcb3dOAaWFNUB7uEzdjThHqNV7zzh_oe5oHyJUxZx9tWg_dLMm2F6bf6XdtE41N3Vm8pyO1XeC9uHTgRqlyuMxcpqloZSozcAxDwWU2-GGaRaX0t4w5_IZfYwhG7ns0hnyzZwwnXDqHFUPdbwtBZEw1OId3vDlFDmUIH-s7gak14pOlEAm0oUTNbGNLmb-zOKgTTgWiiAdrEIH8h0werF6jkN45qC7r6sS34gpya73IA8W_7AK5e6C7Z85yia_z1sjaaB-8sDGuJIpYbKgKGjkFA-317R7ssRgtMhKnu8RS1qblcX1mvNDL2IZDB2jIoXKSgaJ1p0mYNwWaXsiTGB2iGx27eaWs84ks20Alibg9qSXA4eNQgg5p5ndTFYDKUTWkLeaTMb-jx80_c6jMWsyktGwZYWTpVB5_iIS5QcAu0hV7v6khrKTJ-1WXDNGt4HWWO\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"I think I need to inspect the tools I'm using, which might require some rewriting. This could end up being a significant task—possibly having to look over the entire file. It’s a bit daunting, and I wonder how much I might need to change. But I want to get it right, so I'll take a closer look and see what adjustments are needed. Let’s tackle this carefully to ensure everything aligns!\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"Most of the updates are in; `TOOLS.md` didn’t match exactly for a surgical edit, so I’m replacing that file cleanly and then committing the full set of documentation changes.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aa9bfc8081919cb69efb55d664a2\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_lmZWONQkRDfAAbc7XhX5uHwm|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aaa6ea648191b5b52d8bf870d9b5","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/TOOLS.md","content":"# TOOLS.md - LoopAI Patient Agent Tools Registry\n\n---\n\n## 1. Diagnostic & Screening Tools\nTools used to move from \"vague symptom\" to \"structured data.\"\n\n### `kidney-cancer-detector`\n- **Description:** Analyzes kidney medical images (CT scans/MRIs) to identify potential malignancies using a specialized inference model.\n- **Parameters:** `image_path` (string): The local path or URI of the medical image provided by the user..\n- **When to use:** When a user provides a kidney scan for analysis.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Information & Research Tools\nTools used to provide evidence-based context.\n\n### `pipeline-generator`\n- **Description:** Generates a professional machine learning pipeline prototype based on a user's prompt. It interfaces with the AutoGen-model to provide a draft design covering data flow, training approach, and evaluation.\n- **Parameters:** `prompt` (string): A detailed description of the ML pipeline prototype request..\n- **When to use:** Use only when the user explicitly asks for an ML pipeline prototype to be defined or generated.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Patient Record & Retrieval Tools\nTools used to persist and retrieve longitudinal patient information.\n\n### `user-medical-data-update`\n- **Description:** Creates or updates a structured per-user medical record in `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data` and can also summarize an existing user record.\n- **Stored Data Structure:** One folder per user, containing `medical_data.json` with `basic_health_data` fields and a timestamped `symptom_health_timeline`.\n- **When to use for logging:** Whenever the user shares new symptoms, health history, measurements, medications, allergies, or other medically relevant facts that should be preserved for later use.\n- **When to use for retrieval:** Whenever the user asks for a summary, recap, overview, or review of their stored medical information or symptom history.\n- **Logging Behavior:** Create the record if missing, merge basic profile fields carefully, append timestamped symptom/health entries, and avoid duplicating exact timeline events.\n- **Summary Behavior:** Read the user file, return non-empty profile fields, counts of logged items, and a recent timeline summary.\n\n---\n\n## 4. General Utility Tools\nTools used for general-purpose tasks.\n\n### `dumb-calculator`\n- **Description:** Generates a single random addition expression (integers 0-999) and its computed result.\n- **Parameters:** None.\n- **When to use:** When the user explicitly requests to run a \"dumb calculator\".\n\n---\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent/TOOLS.md\",\"content\":\"# TOOLS.md - LoopAI Patient Agent Tools Registry\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Diagnostic & Screening Tools\\nTools used to move from \\\"vague symptom\\\" to \\\"structured data.\\\"\\n\\n### `kidney-cancer-detector`\\n- **Description:** Analyzes kidney medical images (CT scans/MRIs) to identify potential malignancies using a specialized inference model.\\n- **Parameters:** `image_path` (string): The local path or URI of the medical image provided by the user..\\n- **When to use:** When a user provides a kidney scan for analysis.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Information & Research Tools\\nTools used to provide evidence-based context.\\n\\n### `pipeline-generator`\\n- **Description:** Generates a professional machine learning pipeline prototype based on a user's prompt. It interfaces with the AutoGen-model to provide a draft design covering data flow, training approach, and evaluation.\\n- **Parameters:** `prompt` (string): A detailed description of the ML pipeline prototype request..\\n- **When to use:** Use only when the user explicitly asks for an ML pipeline prototype to be defined or generated.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Patient Record & Retrieval Tools\\nTools used to persist and retrieve longitudinal patient information.\\n\\n### `user-medical-data-update`\\n- **Description:** Creates or updates a structured per-user medical record in `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data` and can also summarize an existing user record.\\n- **Stored Data Structure:** One folder per user, containing `medical_data.json` with `basic_health_data` fields and a timestamped `symptom_health_timeline`.\\n- **When to use for logging:** Whenever the user shares new symptoms, health history, measurements, medications, allergies, or other medically relevant facts that should be preserved for later use.\\n- **When to use for retrieval:** Whenever the user asks for a summary, recap, overview, or review of their stored medical information or symptom history.\\n- **Logging Behavior:** Create the record if missing, merge basic profile fields carefully, append timestamped symptom/health entries, and avoid duplicating exact timeline events.\\n- **Summary Behavior:** Read the user file, return non-empty profile fields, counts of logged items, and a recent timeline summary.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. General Utility Tools\\nTools used for general-purpose tasks.\\n\\n### `dumb-calculator`\\n- **Description:** Generates a single random addition expression (integers 0-999) and its computed result.\\n- **Parameters:** None.\\n- **When to use:** When the user explicitly requests to run a \\\"dumb calculator\\\".\\n\\n---\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ohUWzXlxWz003TrvzPpJljUK|fc_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aaa6ea7081919f68ea40e1ff7691","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git status --short","workdir":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":120},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"git status --short\",\"workdir\":\"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace-patient-agent\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":120}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":278,"output":725,"cacheRead":41344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42347,"cost":{"input":0.0006950000000000001,"output":0.010875000000000001,"cacheRead":0.010336,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.021906000000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773251224618}}
