{"type":"message","id":"ae79fad0","parentId":"e28479a7","timestamp":"2026-03-11T17:47:28.391Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Done — I updated the agent’s Markdown configuration so it is explicitly aware of both **logging** and **retrieving/summarizing** stored medical data.\n\n### Updated files\n- `IDENTITY.md`\n- `SOUL.md`\n- `USER.md`\n- `TOOLS.md`\n- `BOOTSTRAP.md`\n- `AGENTS.md`\n\n### What changed\nThe docs now tell the agent to:\n- use **`user-medical-data-update`** as the standard mechanism for structured patient logging\n- use the same skill to **retrieve/summarize** stored medical history\n- distinguish **stored facts** from new interpretation\n- retrieve structured records when the user asks things like:\n  - “what do you know about me?”\n  - “summarize my medical data”\n  - “what symptoms have I reported so far?”\n- include retrieval as part of the normal health loop, not just logging\n\n### Commit\nI also committed the changes in the workspace:\n\n- `6f4b6d1` — `Document medical logging and retrieval workflow`\n\nIf you want, I can now do one more useful improvement: update the docs so the agent also knows how to choose or derive a **stable real user ID** for production logging, instead of test-style IDs.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09e3c41b3bc0a5220169b1aaab5a388191bb88d6e26fa15ae0\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":170,"output":268,"cacheRead":42368,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42806,"cost":{"input":0.00042500000000000003,"output":0.00402,"cacheRead":0.010591999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.015036999999999998}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773251242209}}
